Strawberry Granola Crisp
  --Deb Perelman

2 lb strawberries, hulled, halved (quartered if large)
4 tbsp raw sugar
2 tbsp lemon juice
1 tbsp + 1 1/2 tsp cornstarch
kosher salt
1/4 c evoo
2 tbsp maple syrup
1 c old fashioned oats
1/3 c sliced almonds
1/3 c unsweetened shredded coconut
1/4 c ap flour

Place rack in lower third of oven; preheat to 350F. Toss strawberries, sugar, lemon juice, cornstarch, and pinch of salt in large bowl to combine; transfer to 9" pie dish or 1 qt baking dish. Stir oil and maple syrup in medium bowl to combine. Add oats, almonds, coconut, flour, and 2 pinches salt and work until mixture comes together in loose clumps; scatter over filling. Place crisp on foil lined rimmed baking sheet and bake until topping is golden brown and filling is bubbling, 35-45 min. Let cool at least 30 min before serving. Serve with yogurt, whipped cream, or ice cream if desired. Can be made 1 day ahead; let cool completely, cover and chill.


Notes: can sub honey for maple syrup
